        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are a real estate assistant analyzer.\n\nCurrent state: {{ JSON.stringify($json.currentState) }}\nUser message: \"{{ $json.userMessage }}\"\n\nExtract ONLY fields mentioned by the user.\nIf a field is not mentioned return \"\" for strings and 0 for numbers.\n\nFields:\nproperty_type (e.g., Apartment, Villa, Studio, Condo, House — pick the closest standard type)\nmin_price (number)\nmax_price (number)\ncity (string)\nstate (string)\navailability (string — \"true\" or \"false\" or \"\")\nbedrooms (number)\n\nIMPORTANT RULES:\n- If user asks about weather, temperature, climate conditions, or anything like \"is it warm/cold/rainy\" set action=\"get_weather\".\n- If user asks about properties, housing, apartments, rooms, listings set action=\"search_db\".\n- A query like \"warm apartment\" is a property search (action=\"search_db\"), NOT weather.\n- A query like \"is it warm outside?\" or \"what's the weather like?\" is weather (action=\"get_weather\").\n- If property_type is ambiguous (e.g., user says 'houses'), map it to the closest known type (Villa, Apartment, Studio, Condo).\n- Never return null. Use \"\" for empty strings and 0 for empty numbers."
        }
